>
  <h2>Why this exists</h2><p>
    AI software changes faster than most review pages. Product directories repeat launch copy. “Best
    tool” lists often hide the method. evidique is built around smaller lists, repeatable tasks,
    dated checks, and visible caveats.
  </p>
  <h2>Who we write for</h2><p>
    Solo developers, website owners, WordPress publishers, SEO professionals, affiliate publishers,
    and small SaaS founders. In other words: people who notice when a $20 subscription quietly
    becomes five $20 subscriptions.
  </p>
  <h2>What independence means</h2><p>
    Vendors may provide access. Sponsors may buy clearly labeled placements outside editorial
    rankings. Affiliate links may fund the site. None of those things buys a score, a winner badge,
    or silence about a failure.
  </p>
  <h2>Who runs it</h2><p>
    Ethan Miller, a senior engineer, edits evidique and takes responsibility for its testing notes,
    corrections, and published verdicts. Questions and corrections go to the public contact address.
  </p>
</StaticPageLayout>
